Key Concepts to Remember
Task 7 - Authentication:

Kerberos is the modern default (not NetNTLM)

TGT (Ticket Granting Ticket) is used to request TGS (Ticket Granting Service)

Neither protocol transmits passwords over the network

Task 8 - Domain Structure:

Tree: Multiple domains sharing the same namespace (like canada.thm.local, usa.thm.local)

Trust Relationship: Formal connection between domains allowing cross-domain access

Without a trust, users from one domain cannot access resources in another

